
Login your server which you want rubyencoder.

cd /usr/local/

Download tar file from rubyencoder.com

https://www.rubyencoder.com/profile.html?cm_id=151&action=download&id=7ea050467fba29aee7452d3e680a920c

rubyencoder-2.2-evaluation-linux-i386.tar.gz

tar -zxvf rubyencoder-2.2-evaluation-linux-i386.tar.gz
mv rubyencoder-2.2-evaluation rubyencoder

./rubyencoder/bin/rubyencoder

You will get license agreement page.. Once completed you will get Registration key.

ex:

Web site:         http://www.rubyencoder.com/
Registration key: 6385F09177121F260080C680A9E9F7F2

Download the license file and copy it into this directory:

/usr/local/rubyencoder/bin/


Go to your https://www.rubyencoder.com/profile.html license page and entry that registration key to get the license files.

Download encode.lic file and move /usr/local/rubyencoder/bin/ folder

Thats it.

example encoder command

/usr/local/rubyencoder/bin/rubyencoder  --ruby 2.1.0 --ruby 2.2.0 -r "/Gemini-poc-mgnt/*.rb" >> /home/rubyencoder.log
